{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_45","type":"agent_message","text":"Reproducing `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ognl:ognl:3.3.5` with the required GraalVM showed the failure was not a missing-metadata error. The actual blocker was a wrong test expectation in [ObjectPropertyAccessorTest.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/7430-44251cbd/tests/src/ognl/ognl/3.3.5/src/test/java/ognl/ognl/ObjectPropertyAccessorTest.java:48): when setter access is denied, `ognl.ObjectPropertyAccessor#setPossibleProperty` returns `OgnlRuntime.NotFound` and does not assign the value. I updated the test to assert that real contract.\n\nVerification used the same pinned `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME`, and `native-image --version` matched the required `25.0.3 / Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+9.1`. After the change, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ognl:ognl:3.3.5` passed successfully. No metadata JSON change was needed for the reproduced failure."}}
